        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/4–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Benninghoff</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-07">April [7?],
                            1947</date>.<lb/>[Received April 13—8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Advance information is requested concerning any American participation in
                    proposed Chinese expedition from Tsingtao.</p>
                <p>Can we expect US Navy, diplomatic courier, or correspondents? <pb facs="0521" n="511" xml:id="pg_511"/> Also would appreciate instructions if any which
                    Dept or Embassy may have, especially reference last parts mytel 55.<note n="65" xml:id="d420fn1">April 5, 10 a.m., <ref target="#pg_509">p.
                        509</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Dept as 57; in reply to Nanking’s 8, April 2;<note n="66" xml:id="d420fn2">Not found in Department files.</note> see mytel 55, April 5.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Benninghoff</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
